oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Found items from the Gilbert Kenedy and James McKeown home place
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: McKeown home place near Kincannon's Ferry in Meigs County, Tenn. which had a blacksmith on property. William McKeown served as a private in the 5th Tenn. Cav., CSA. The found items include a broad axes, two adzes (mattocks)" a small stirrup, a small double vice, hammers, cowbells, and pewter buttons.
